# 4. 大事な気持ちを

Mizuki's Sister: Alright, we're here!
Mizuki's Sister: Where should we go first? Any shops that you'd like to visit, Mizuki?
Elementary School Mizuki: ...
Mizuki's Sister: How about the decor shop we always go to? Oh, a new jewelry store seems to have opened up on the second floor. Why don't we go check that out?
Elementary School Mizuki: Huh? A jewelry store...?
Elementary School Mizuki: (I wonder what it's like... Maybe they have some cute stuff.)
Classmate B: But it's kinda weird that you're wearing it.
Elementary School Mizuki: Oh...
Elementary School Mizuki: No, I'll pass.
Mizuki's Sister: Okay...
Mizuki's Sister: Then, let's have something sweet to eat...!
Mizuki's Sister: I'll go buy us some crepes. You sit tight here on this bench, okay?
Elementary School Mizuki: Okay...
Elementary School Mizuki: (I'm making Sis worry too much...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (She brought me here because she noticed that I wasn't feeling great...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (And yet, I...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (But if I don't change...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (Everyone's gonna keep saying I'm weird...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (I don't want that to happen...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (The way they tell me... It's like me being different means I don't belong there with them...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (That hurts so much... And it makes me feel so lonely...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (So, I...)
Elementary School Mizuki: Oh...
Elementary School Mizuki: (The one-piece in that shop's window... Is it new? It wasn't there when Sis and I went the other day.)
Elementary School Mizuki: (It's got so many bows and frills too...)
Elementary School Mizuki: It's really cute...
Elementary School Mizuki: This is so cool! These shoes and this ribbon are so adorable, and they even go perfectly with the blouse you made for me...!
Elementary School Mizuki: (No...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (What I really want is...)
Mizuki's Sister: I'm back with the crepes! I got you a strawberry one, Mizuki! I know it's your favorite!
Elementary School Mizuki: ...
Elementary School Mizuki: Sis...
Elementary School Mizuki: Am... Am I weird?
Mizuki's Sister: No, you're not weird. Why are you asking such a thing...?
Elementary School Mizuki: Then, why's everyone else calling me that...?
Mizuki's Sister: ... Oh, um...
Elementary School Mizuki: The thing is... I feel like I need to stop liking all the stuff that I think is cute.
Mizuki's Sister: What...?
Elementary School Mizuki: Because everyone will stop saying that I'm weird if I do... I won't have to feel this way anymore...
Elementary School Mizuki: But...
Elementary School Mizuki: I really love those kinds of things... And all the clothes that you make, Sis.
Elementary School Mizuki: I don't wanna say the opposite of that...
Mizuki's Sister: Mizuki...
Mizuki's Sister: I'm so sorry...
Mizuki's Sister: I had no idea this was bothering you so much. I really need to apologize for that...
Mizuki's Sister: And I understand what you're saying...
Mizuki's Sister: Being put down by others... Not being able to talk about the things you like... They both must be causing you so much pain.
Elementary School Mizuki: ...
Mizuki's Sister: But this is what I believe...
Mizuki's Sister: I think you should keep liking all the things you feel are cute...
Elementary School Mizuki: What?
Mizuki's Sister: That's what makes up who you are, right...?
Elementary School Mizuki: But... Then they'll...
Mizuki's Sister: I know... They'll keep saying all those terrible things to you.
Mizuki's Sister: And to prevent that from happening, you might start to feel like you can't talk about the things you like as much...
Mizuki's Sister: But I don't think you should stop liking what you like to fit in with everyone else...
Mizuki's Sister: Because you're not weird at all, Mizuki...
Mizuki's Sister: I love how you love things that are cute.
Elementary School Mizuki: Sis...
Mizuki's Sister: Which is why, Mizuki... I want you to cherish your true feelings.
Elementary School Mizuki: (So, it's okay...?)
Elementary School Mizuki: (I can keep liking the things that I think are cute...?)
Elementary School Mizuki: (I am scared of what everyone else is gonna say...)
Elementary School Mizuki: (But if Sis says that I'm not weird... If she loves me the way that I am...)
Elementary School Mizuki: *Nod*
Mizuki's Sister: Alright... After we finish eating our crepes, would you mind tagging along as I shop for a few things?
Mizuki's Sister: I've been looking for the right buttons to use for this new outfit I've been designing.
Elementary School Mizuki: Huh? Buttons...?
Mizuki's Sister: Yes, it's going to be for myself... But I also want to make it so you really like it too, Mizuki!
Mizuki's Sister: Which is why I need you to tell me more about all the things you like.
Elementary School Mizuki: Oh...
Elementary School Mizuki: Okay...!
Mizuki: (Some really awful things happened to me after that...)
Mizuki: (I even tried not being myself because they just kept sapping away at my energy.)
Mizuki: (But because Sis said back then that it's okay for me to cherish my true feelings...)
Mizuki: (Despite all the things that did end up happening to me, I still like all the cute stuff I did back then.)
Mizuki's Sister: Mizuki? Is something wrong?
Mizuki: No, nothing's wrong...! I was just reminiscing about the past a little.
Mizuki: I always had so much fun going out shopping with you while wearing the clothes that you made.
Mizuki's Sister: Hehe. I did make quite a lot just for you.
Mizuki's Sister: Oh yeah, remember how you used to stare into my room while I was on my sewing machine? That was always so cute.
Mizuki: Wait, you remember that?
Mizuki's Sister: Of course I remember! You made me so happy every time you told me the buttons and frills I chose to use were cute.
Mizuki: Well... That's enough about me. Lemme hear more about what you've been up to, Sis!
Mizuki: I have so many questions that I wanna ask you! How have things been over there? What's work been like?
Mizuki's Sister: Hehe. Okay. Where should I start?
